            , who gave him the Plate as a Pledge for some Money he lent him to carry him down to his Ship at Chatham; but the Jury did not believe him, and the Prosecutor deposed that the Prisoner knew the Plate very well, having so long constantly made use of it, and his Mark being thereon. The Jury found him <rs id="t17190708-26-verdict138" type="verdictDescription">
